<br>
PRE-patch it was still hard to say.  The SK that stands there and tries to debuff you / LT you is a dead SK.  The SK that bashes/melees/HTs you has a chance.  Keeping up epic + Spellshield is kewl tho cuz usually they break thru epic skin and get excited and pop HT only to have Spellshield eat it.<br>
<br>
Usually I just run around and yonder/Draught or Yonder/Lure.  If I see them casting - use a big boom.  They're stupid for trying to cast ANYTHING on you.  Engulfing Darkness?  Big deal - if you are tactically using yonder/Draught as a means of doing damage - who cares about being snared anywayz - yer yondering as a means to gain distance.<br>
<br>
Anywayz - like I said, too hard to really post some tactics since new resistance changes - but I imagine playing the yonder/nuke game still works and if they stop to cast soemthing, you can stop to cast the big boom.<br>
