IMO best line up is: Telecope, See invis,Jboots, chill sight,Ultravision, PR flower, resitant, Elemental, Shield of the arcane, Manasink, Shield of the Magi. U click telescope and See invis So u have 2 free slot u can dispell. Then if U get snared, U can dispell it right away w/o having to strip all your buffs (as u would have to do with your setup) I also have horse and Run 3 so dont care much for Jboots, bu this way, with Jboots of top, I can dispell snare right away =)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Wizard: With the new PoP spell, wiz versus Wiz has become more then just who has the most HP and who casts the 1st Lure. <br>
IE: If I'd take Lightadam for example, who has about twice my HP unbuffed, I can't just lure him, cause even if I get 1st cast, he can waste me in no time. he also has way better spell then me. so the trick is to not let him cast right?  Telekin is useless versus him since he resist it all the time, so all I can do is cast Draugh of Thunded and Lure of ro, depending what he casts and all.<br>
<br>
Shaman: Those are a pain IMO. the one I fight have more then 5K HP. If they have the AA root and the Mini pet whatever it's called, you are pretty much dead. so to Tassaddar, Kylt and Ramic, I say Manaburn cause there is no way in hell I can kill them on on one with AA root and mini pet up. They have more HP then our rogues =/  And damn You Kylt for your HP over 6.2K buffed!  if I had KEI, I wouldn't of got KS'd by Smilo ^_~<br>
<br>
Druid: Lure, Lure, Draugh of Thunder, lure = down Unless They have a bugged horse and shout in Zone &quot; haha You gimp, you can't kill me&quot; duh, I can't kill u if from 1 feet away, Im OOR of spell cast huh Gideaon.<br>
<br>
SK : Yonder + levit + lure all the way with some draugh of thunder.<br>
<br>
Bards: huh...  if the bard is smart, u cannot really kill him cause he runs too fast! so Know your spell effects, and avoid their songs.<br>
<br>
Mage: haha if U have a horse, Dispell the pet, then run away.... far far away....  then come back, and watch the mage cry as he goes down , seeing that his pet will be too slow to come to the rescue.  Or U can just Nuke the mage to death, while tanking his pet , putting your back in a corner, so it does not interrupt u.<br>
<br>
Pally: Avoid the blade, Yonder, Lure are your best friend. If u know that pally has weak MR, be a meanie and lure him down to about 1 1/2 bubble of HP, and Telekin him, then lure once more. So he can't use LoH ^_~<br>
<br>
chanter: Rapture is a biotch...  So again, draugh of Thunder and lure or draugh of ro, depending on resist.<br>
<br>
Warrior. Lure then down.... if u have the mana. 8K HP to lure down can be a biotch <br>
<br>
Ranger: Hide behind trees and stuff to avoid the arrows, cause AM3 ranger hurts!<br>
<br>
Rogues: Just lure them down, should not take long =/<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Note that I don't have most of my lvl 63-65 spells, otherwise Tears of axywhatever would be fun to play with, along with SoS.<br>
<br>
