60th Wizard of TZ</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=uskerz>UskeRZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/19/03 9:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mid 50's tactics</span><hr size=1> Well I have seen all these tactics for 60+ and I would like to add some advice for the PvP'r in the mid 50's.  Being in a PK guild for sometime now I am constantly at war with someone.  Let me first say that i am a 55 wiz with 10aa's.   My primary place to PK is GD, KC, DL, VL, and HHK.   Here is my buff line up:<br>
<br>
telescope<br>
shifting sight<br>
chill sight<br>
jboots<br>
shield of magi<br>
Familiar<br>
PoM flower (or elemental shielding spell)<br>
PoM flower (or resistant skin)<br>
Manaskin<br>
c3 (when able)<br>
gmr (when able)<br>
levi or dmf<br>
<br>
For spells i use:<br>
Lure of Flame<br>
Ice Comet<br>
Tishans Discord<br>
Anull Magic<br>
Root<br>
Yonder<br>
Gate<br>
Harvest<br>
<br>
I always click off telescope and shifting sight for dot slots.   Always leave at least one open slot for WD it can kill you straight out.  It is nasty.  Ok, now that you are buffed it is time to fight.<br>
<br>
vs Druids:  Let me first say these guys are pretty nasty.  I usually open with dispell (druid w/o buffs is a dead druid).  By now if the druid is smart he has landed WD.  Anul yourself.  Now commence the beat down of a tree hugger.  Biggest thing vs a druid is to NOT chase him, unless he is almost dead.  If you chase him there is a good chance you will just lose him and that is what he wants.  I just wait where i was or hide somewhere out of sight and spam my IC key until he is in range (he will be tracking you).  Needless to say dont let him gate (this is where stun comes in.<br>
<br>
vs Melee: Yonder, Lure, Lure, IC... pretty easy, it is a good idea to dispell warriors because it is a bitch to lure down 6k hp if he has aego.<br>
<br>
vs Paladins:  Not worth the time and mana.  Honestly.. they can out heal your nukes, if they have loh up you are screwed... only way i ever beat paladins is if i can land bio orb on them and then i get a few good IC's off and lure them mid heal.<br>
<br>
vs Shadow Knights:  They are extremely easy, follow the yonder, lure, lure, IC.  Dont let them get within mele range because the easiest way to ruin your day is for them to chew through rune and pop HT.  If you are snared it isnt a big deal, yonder takes care of that.<br>
<br>
vs Clerics:  Again not worth the time or effort.  I usually dispell them down to nothing and gate.  At least i have the satisfaction of wasting their peridot.<br>
<br>
vs Shamans:  If you can blind them you will win... if not they are going to go defensive and heal themselves.<br>
<br>
vs Enchanters: If you sneak up on them you will win.  If i land an IC before he knows what hits him i can finish him with a lure mid tash/mez.  Enchanters have very little hp. On the other hand, if they sneak up on you you may be in a world of trouble.<br>
<br>
vs Mage:  Run off and root pet.  Return to nuke down the mage.  Very easy tactic and always works.<br>
<br>
vs Necro:  Same tactic as before, run off root pet and return to nuke the necro.. I like to nuke, yonder, yonder and then start spamming my IC button so i cast as soon as they are in range.  Remember that splurt can be anulled.   You can always leave splurt on you for about 30 seconds because it does about 20% of it's damage in the beginning of the spell.  Other then that Necro's are really easy.<br>
<br>
Well I hope that that helps you.  If you have any questions send me a tell on Rallos Zek.<br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
Uske Yaaro<br>
55 Evoker<br>
&lt;The Curse&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chifiir>Chifiir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/20/03 2:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> WTF?</span><hr size=1> Maybe we just have a different class of player on Sullon Zek, but the things you guys are posting for &quot;tactics&quot; count on really really really stupid oppenents who have no idea about PvP or resists.<br>
<br>
Druids will range-ES you you down.  It'll bypass your epic/skins and eat at your crappy hps.  They'll stay at max range and dance.  They'll outheal any nukes you DO happen to land.<br>
<br>
Pet classes will put the pet on you.  Assuming you have a horse, you're outdoors, and you can channel through the pet (quadding bst/mage pets are tough to channel through) you might be able to get away...and right into the Shaman's big DoTs, assuming they didn't DoT you while you tried to debuff pets.  Or you'll walk into FoT from the mage.  The BST might be doable if you can catch him and get him to stay in range long enough to actually cast on him.<br>
<br>
Ice Comet?  In PvP?  Hihi 90 pts of damge.  IF you can get off that long-assed spell.  Draughts?  Worthless in &quot;even&quot; PvP due to resists until level 61+ draughts.<br>
<br>
UskeRZ, tell me - how are you going to blind a shaman of approx even level to you?  Orb him and watch it bounce off his MR?  <br>
<br>
Maybe people play differently on RZ, but most of those &quot;tactics&quot; simply won't work against a player with a clue.<br>
<br>
You vs Rapture chanter = your_death<br>
<br>
Why?  Resists and the 66% spell nerf.  They don't have to Tash you to Rapture you and their gear will give them decent resists vs Draughts.  You tag them twice for ~900 damage they've got you locked down.<br>
<br>
Melee = yonder lure lure IC?  Dude, who are you fighting that they've got that few hps?    Even low-end 50 SKs have over 2k hps and that ICs not even worth the paper it's scribed on at that level.  You'll need at least 5 Lures to drop him, and that's with him not-tapping and with your taking big melee damage from him.  With Warriors I hope you have a LOT of mana.  A 3k warrior will take 6-7 Lures and they're not going to just stand there and let you cast on 'em.  One or two bashes and you're dead.<br>
<br>
Rangers?  They'll out shoot you at range and get better crits to boot.  Give them AM3 and you're best off finding a good place to hide and hope they don't track you.<br>
<br>
If your tactics work on RZ, maybe I should switch servers 'cause they sure don't work on SZ.  =/<br>
<br>
-Szii Uln'hyrr<br>
